= TuringArena - Create algorithmic challenges

TuringArena is a toolkit to define challenges which require an algorithmic solution,
and to automatically test the code of solutions.

For the documentation see http://www.turingarena.org[the TuringArena website].

== Getting started

TuringArena requires *Python 3.6*.

We recommend using a python virtualenv to use this software from source
(see http://virtualenvwrapper.readthedocs.io/[the virtualenvwrapper documentation]).

Commands to setup python and use a virtualenv (on Debian, using virtualenvwrapper):

[source,bash]
  $ sudo apt-get install python3.6 python3-virtualenv virtualenvwrapper # install virtualenvwrapper
  $ mkvirtualenv -p /usr/bin/python3.6 turingarena # create a virualenv named 'turingarena'
  $ workon turingarena # use your shiny virtualenv
  $ deactivate # exit the virtualenv

Once you set-up your virtualenv,
clone or download the repository (follow GitHub instruction)
then `cd` into the cloned/download folder and run:

[source,bash]
  $ workon turingarena
  $ python setup.py develop
